[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `assess_image_quality(bucket, image_key)`. Before the classification model ever sees an image, we confirm it's actually gradable. A blurry, poorly-centered, or underexposed fundus image will produce unreliable predictions. This gate prevents the most common source of false negatives in screening programs.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def download_image_from_s3(bucket: str, key: str) -> Image.Image:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Download a fundus image from S3 and return it as a PIL Image.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         bucket: S3 bucket name
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         key: S3 object key (path to the image file)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         PIL Image object ready for processing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = s3_client.get_object(Bucket=bucket, Key=key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     image_bytes = response["Body"].read()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return Image.open(BytesIO(image_bytes))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def calculate_sharpness(image: Image.Image) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Estimate image sharpness using Laplacian variance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The Laplacian operator detects edges. A sharp image has many strong edges
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (high variance of the Laplacian). A blurry image has weak, diffuse edges
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (low variance). This is a standard focus quality metric.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For retinal images, sharpness matters because microaneurysms (the earliest
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sign of diabetic retinopathy) are tiny dots. If the image is blurry enough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to smear those dots into the background, the model will miss them.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Normalized sharpness score between 0.0 and 1.0.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert to grayscale for edge detection.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gray = np.array(image.convert("L"), dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Laplacian kernel (approximation using second derivatives).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This highlights regions of rapid intensity change (edges).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     laplacian = np.array([[0, 1, 0], [1, -4, 1], [0, 1, 0]], dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convolve the image with the Laplacian kernel.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     from scipy.signal import convolve2d
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     filtered = convolve2d(gray, laplacian, mode="same", boundary="symm")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Variance of the Laplacian response. Higher = sharper.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     variance = np.var(filtered)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Normalize to 0-1 range. These bounds are empirical for fundus images.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # A variance below 100 is very blurry; above 1500 is very sharp.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalized = min(max((variance - 100) / 1400, 0.0), 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return normalized
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def calculate_illumination_uniformity(image: Image.Image) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check whether the image has adequate and uniform illumination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Fundus images should have a bright central region (the retina illuminated
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     by the camera flash) with gradual falloff toward the edges. Problems:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Underexposed: everything is dark, pathology invisible
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Overexposed: washed out, no contrast between structures
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Uneven: one side bright, other side dark (camera misalignment)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Normalized illumination score between 0.0 and 1.0.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gray = np.array(image.convert("L"), dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check overall brightness (mean pixel value).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mean_brightness = np.mean(gray)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check dynamic range (standard deviation of pixel values).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # A good fundus image uses most of the 0-255 range.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     std_brightness = np.std(gray)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Penalize images that are too dark (mean < 50) or too bright (mean > 200).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     brightness_score = 1.0 - abs(mean_brightness - 125) / 125
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Penalize images with low dynamic range (flat histogram).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     range_score = min(std_brightness / 50, 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return (brightness_score + range_score) / 2
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def calculate_field_of_view(image: Image.Image) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Estimate whether the image captures adequate retinal area.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     A proper fundus image should show the optic disc and macula within the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     field of view. If the patient blinked, the camera was misaligned, or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the pupil was too small, you get a partial image that's ungradable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is a simplified check based on the circular retinal area visible
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     in the image. A real implementation would use landmark detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (find the optic disc and macula explicitly).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Normalized field of view score between 0.0 and 1.0.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gray = np.array(image.convert("L"), dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Fundus images typically show a bright circular region (the retina)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # against a dark background. Threshold to find the illuminated area.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     threshold = 30  # pixels brighter than this are "retina"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     retinal_pixels = np.sum(gray > threshold)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_pixels = gray.size
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The illuminated area should be at least 60% of the image frame.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Less than that suggests partial capture or severe vignetting.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     coverage = retinal_pixels / total_pixels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalized = min(coverage / 0.60, 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return normalized
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def detect_artifacts(image: Image.Image) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check for common artifacts: dust spots, eyelash shadows, reflections.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Artifacts can mimic pathology (a dust spot looks like a hemorrhage) or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hide pathology (an eyelash shadow obscures the macula). Either way,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the image is unreliable for grading.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This simplified version checks for unusually bright spots (reflections)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and unusually dark linear features (eyelashes). A production system
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     would use a trained artifact detection model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Normalized artifact-free score between 0.0 and 1.0.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Higher = fewer artifacts = better quality.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gray = np.array(image.convert("L"), dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check for specular reflections (very bright spots).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     bright_pixels = np.sum(gray > 250)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     bright_ratio = bright_pixels / gray.size
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check for very dark regions that shouldn't be there (eyelash shadows).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Exclude the natural dark border of the fundus image.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     center_region = gray[
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         gray.shape[0] // 4 : 3 * gray.shape[0] // 4,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         gray.shape[1] // 4 : 3 * gray.shape[1] // 4,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dark_in_center = np.sum(center_region < 20)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dark_ratio = dark_in_center / center_region.size
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Score: penalize for reflections and dark artifacts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     reflection_penalty = min(bright_ratio * 50, 0.5)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     shadow_penalty = min(dark_ratio * 20, 0.5)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return max(1.0 - reflection_penalty - shadow_penalty, 0.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def assess_image_quality(bucket: str, image_key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full quality assessment pipeline on a fundus image.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     All four quality dimensions must pass their respective thresholds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for the image to be considered gradable. If any dimension fails,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the image is rejected with a specific reason so the camera operator
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     knows what to fix (retake with better focus, ask patient to open
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eyes wider, clean the lens, etc.).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         bucket: S3 bucket containing the image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         image_key: S3 key of the fundus image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with gradable (bool), quality_score (float), and if failed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         the reason and recommendation for recapture.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     image = download_image_from_s3(bucket, image_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Run each quality check independently.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scores = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "field_of_view": calculate_field_of_view(image),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sharpness": calculate_sharpness(image),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "illumination": calculate_illumination_uniformity(image),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "artifact": detect_artifacts(image),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Find any dimensions that failed their threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     failures = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         dim: score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for dim, score in scores.items()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if score < QUALITY_THRESHOLDS[dim]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Overall quality is the minimum across all dimensions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # One bad dimension makes the whole image ungradable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     overall_quality = min(scores.values())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if failures:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Identify the worst-performing dimension for the recapture instruction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         worst_dim = min(failures, key=failures.get)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recommendations = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "field_of_view": "Reposition camera. Ensure optic disc and macula are visible.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sharpness": "Refocus the camera. Ask patient to fixate on the target.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "illumination": "Adjust flash intensity. Check for media opacities (cataracts).",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "artifact": "Clean the lens. Ask patient to open eyes wider. Check for reflections.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Image quality FAILED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             extra={"image_key": image_key, "worst_dimension": worst_dim,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                    "scores": scores},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "gradable": False,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "quality_score": overall_quality,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "scores": scores,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "reason": f"Failed quality check: {worst_dim} ({failures[worst_dim]:.2f} < {QUALITY_THRESHOLDS[worst_dim]})",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "recommendation": recommendations[worst_dim],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Image quality PASSED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extra={"image_key": image_key, "quality_score": overall_quality},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "gradable": True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "quality_score": overall_quality,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "scores": scores,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Model Inference (DR Classification)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `classify_retinal_image(bucket, image_key)`. The fundus image is preprocessed and sent to the SageMaker endpoint hosting the deep learning model. The model outputs probabilities for each ICDR severity level plus a separate DME probability.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def preprocess_for_model(image: Image.Image) -> bytes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Preprocess a fundus image for model inference.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The preprocessing must exactly match what was done during model training.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Typical steps for retinal models:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Resize to the model's expected input dimensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Normalize pixel values to [0, 1] or [-1, 1] range
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Apply any color normalization (some models expect specific color balance)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Serialize to the format the endpoint expects
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Serialized image tensor as bytes, ready for the SageMaker endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Resize to model input dimensions. Use LANCZOS for high-quality downsampling.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Fundus images are typically 2000x2000+; the model expects 512x512.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     resized = image.resize(MODEL_INPUT_SIZE, Image.LANCZOS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert to numpy array and normalize to [0, 1] range.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     img_array = np.array(resized, dtype=np.float32) / 255.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Some models expect channel-first format (C, H, W) instead of (H, W, C).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check your model's documentation. We'll use channel-last here.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # img_array shape: (512, 512, 3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Serialize as JSON with the pixel values as a nested list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Alternative formats: application/x-npy, application/x-image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # JSON is verbose but universally supported by SageMaker endpoints.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payload = json.dumps({"instances": [img_array.tolist()]})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return payload.encode("utf-8")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_retinal_image(bucket: str, image_key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Send a fundus image to the DR classification model and get predictions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The model outputs a probability distribution over the 5 ICDR severity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     levels plus a separate DME probability. This gives downstream logic
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the flexibility to apply different thresholds for different clinical
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     contexts rather than being locked into a single hard classification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         bucket: S3 bucket containing the image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         image_key: S3 key of the fundus image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with per-level probabilities, DME probability, model version,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         and inference time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     image = download_image_from_s3(bucket, image_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payload = preprocess_for_model(image)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Invoke the SageMaker endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is a synchronous call; it blocks until inference completes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Typical latency: 2-5 seconds for a single image on a GPU endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = sagemaker_runtime.invoke_endpoint(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         EndpointName=SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ContentType="application/json",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=payload,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Parse the model response.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = json.loads(response["Body"].read().decode("utf-8"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Expected response structure from the model:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   "predictions": [[0.02, 0.05, 0.78, 0.12, 0.03]],  # ICDR probabilities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   "dme_predictions": [[0.85, 0.15]],                  # [no_dme, dme]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   "model_version": "v2.3.1"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     probabilities = result["predictions"][0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dme_probs = result["dme_predictions"][0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     predictions = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "no_dr_probability": probabilities[0],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "mild_npdr_probability": probabilities[1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "moderate_npdr_probability": probabilities[2],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "severe_npdr_probability": probabilities[3],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "pdr_probability": probabilities[4],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "dme_probability": dme_probs[1],  # probability of DME present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "model_version": result.get("model_version", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "severity_levels": SEVERITY_LEVELS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Model inference complete",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extra={"image_key": image_key, "model_version": predictions["model_version"]},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return predictions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Clinical Decision Logic
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `apply_clinical_decision(predictions)`. This is where model output becomes a clinical action. The mapping from probabilities to referral decisions is the most clinically sensitive part of the system.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def apply_clinical_decision(predictions: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Map model predictions to a clinical screening decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The decision logic handles four scenarios:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Model is uncertain (max probability below confidence threshold) -> human review
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. High probability of sight-threatening disease (severe/PDR) -> urgent referral
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Referable DR detected (moderate+) -> routine referral
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. DME detected (independent of DR severity) -> routine referral
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     5. No referable disease -> clear for annual rescreening
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The thresholds here are configurable and MUST be validated on your specific
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient population before clinical deployment. A screening program's operating
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     point is a tradeoff between sensitivity (catching all disease) and specificity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (not overwhelming ophthalmology with false referrals).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions: Output from classify_retinal_image()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with decision, urgency, severity_grade, and supporting probabilities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Calculate the probability of referable DR (moderate NPDR or worse).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is the key metric for the referral decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     referable_probability = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["moderate_npdr_probability"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         + predictions["severe_npdr_probability"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         + predictions["pdr_probability"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Calculate urgency: severe NPDR or PDR requires expedited referral
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # because these stages carry high risk of imminent vision loss.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     urgent_probability = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["severe_npdr_probability"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         + predictions["pdr_probability"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Determine the highest-probability severity grade for the record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     prob_list = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["no_dr_probability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["mild_npdr_probability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["moderate_npdr_probability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["severe_npdr_probability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions["pdr_probability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_idx = prob_list.index(max(prob_list))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     severity_grade = SEVERITY_LEVELS[max_idx]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_probability = max(prob_list)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Decision logic with confidence gating.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if max_probability < CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Model is not confident enough for an autonomous decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Route to a human grader (ophthalmologist or trained reader).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # This is a SAFETY feature, not a failure mode.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         decision = "HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         urgency = "routine"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif urgent_probability >= URGENT_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # High probability of sight-threatening disease. Urgent referral.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Patient needs ophthalmology within days, not weeks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         decision = "URGENT_REFERRAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         urgency = "urgent"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif referable_probability >= REFERABLE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Referable DR detected. Routine ophthalmology referral.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Patient needs to be seen within 2-4 weeks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         decision = "ROUTINE_REFERRAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         urgency = "routine"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif predictions["dme_probability"] >= DME_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # DME detected independent of DR severity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Macular edema can occur at any DR stage and independently
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # threatens central vision. Requires referral.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         decision = "ROUTINE_REFERRAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         urgency = "routine"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         severity_grade = f"{severity_grade} with DME"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # No referable disease detected.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Patient is safe to screen again in 12 months.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         decision = "NO_REFERRAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         urgency = "none"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "decision": decision,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "urgency": urgency,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "severity_grade": severity_grade,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "referable_probability": round(referable_probability, 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "dme_probability": round(predictions["dme_probability"], 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "urgent_probability": round(urgent_probability, 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "max_probability": round(max_probability, 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "model_version": predictions["model_version"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Clinical decision rendered",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extra={"decision": decision, "severity": severity_grade},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Store Results and Trigger Actions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `store_and_act(patient_id, image_key, quality_result, predictions, decision)`. Every screening event gets a complete audit record, and the appropriate downstream action is triggered based on the clinical decision.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_screening_result(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     image_key: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     quality_result: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     predictions: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     decision: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write the complete screening record to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This record is the authoritative output of the screening pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     It must contain everything needed for:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Clinical use (what was the result, what action was taken)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Regulatory audit (which model version, what were the raw predictions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Quality monitoring (track performance over time)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Reprocessing (if a model is updated, rerun on stored images)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     DynamoDB requires Decimal for numeric values, not float.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is a known gotcha that will throw a TypeError if you forget.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     screening_id = f"scr-{datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime('%Y-%m%d')}-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:5]}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "screening_id": screening_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "screening_date": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "image_key": image_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "quality_score": Decimal(str(round(quality_result["quality_score"], 3))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "severity_grade": decision["severity_grade"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "referable_probability": Decimal(str(decision["referable_probability"])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "dme_probability": Decimal(str(decision["dme_probability"])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "clinical_decision": decision["decision"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "urgency": decision["urgency"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "model_version": decision["model_version"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Store raw predictions for audit trail. Convert all floats to Decimal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "raw_predictions": json.loads(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             json.dumps(predictions), parse_float=Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": "COMPLETE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results_table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Screening result stored",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extra={"screening_id": screening_id, "patient_id": patient_id},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def trigger_downstream_action(patient_id: str, screening_id: str, decision: dict):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Trigger the appropriate notification based on the clinical decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - URGENT_REFERRAL: Immediate provider notification (SNS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - ROUTINE_REFERRAL: Standard referral notification (SNS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED: Add to reading queue (DynamoDB)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - NO_REFERRAL: Patient notification of normal result (SNS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     message_base = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "screening_id": screening_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "severity_grade": decision["severity_grade"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "decision": decision["decision"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "timestamp": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if decision["decision"] == "URGENT_REFERRAL":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sns_client.publish(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             TopicArn=SNS_URGENT_REFERRAL_TOPIC,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Subject="URGENT: Diabetic Retinopathy Screening - Immediate Referral Required",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Message=json.dumps(message_base),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Urgent referral notification sent", extra={"patient_id": patient_id})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif decision["decision"] == "ROUTINE_REFERRAL":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sns_client.publish(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             TopicArn=SNS_ROUTINE_REFERRAL_TOPIC,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Subject="Diabetic Retinopathy Screening - Referral Recommended",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Message=json.dumps(message_base),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Routine referral notification sent", extra={"patient_id": patient_id})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif decision["decision"] == "HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Add to reading queue for a qualified human grader.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         reading_queue_table.put_item(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Item={
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "screening_id": screening_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "image_key": message_base.get("image_key", ""),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "raw_predictions": json.loads(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     json.dumps(decision), parse_float=Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "priority": "standard",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "status": "PENDING_REVIEW",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "queued_at": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Added to human reading queue", extra={"screening_id": screening_id})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # NO_REFERRAL: normal result, schedule next annual screening.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         message_base["next_screening_due"] = "12 months from screening date"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sns_client.publish(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             TopicArn=SNS_NORMAL_RESULT_TOPIC,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Subject="Diabetic Retinopathy Screening - Normal Result",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Message=json.dumps(message_base),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Normal result notification sent", extra={"patient_id": patient_id})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Full Pipeline Function
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This assembles all four steps into a single callable function. The print statements show progress so you can trace execution during development.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_screening_pipeline(patient_id: str, bucket: str, image_key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Execute the complete diabetic retinopathy screening pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Steps:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Assess image quality (reject ungradable images immediately)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Classify the retinal image (invoke DR model)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Apply clinical decision logic (map predictions to actions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Store results and trigger downstream actions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Unique patient identifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         bucket: S3 bucket containing the fundus image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         image_key: S3 key of the fundus image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Complete screening record dict, or quality failure dict if image rejected.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"\n{'='*60}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"DIABETIC RETINOPATHY SCREENING PIPELINE")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"Patient: {patient_id}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"Image: s3://{bucket}/{image_key}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"{'='*60}\n")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Step 1: Quality Assessment ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("[Step 1/4] Assessing image quality...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     quality_result = assess_image_quality(bucket, image_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not quality_result["gradable"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"  ❌ Image REJECTED: {quality_result['reason']}")
